<br>
I don't doubt that many believe that a War time economy is a good economy, or good for the nation.<br>
<br>
However, it should be noted that Korea, Vietnam, and the Persian Gulf wars didn't improve the US economy. In fact, it is arguable that both the Korean war and the Vietnam conflict put the US into the recession of the 70s. <br>
<br>
The Persian Gulf war disrupted the US economy and didn't help it. Oil prices rose sharply (went from $15 per barrel to $40!), consumer confidence (which drives Wall Street) fell sharply. The US spent $60 Billion dollars adding to the growing deficit of the time.<br>
<br>
The US economy is fragile at this time. Spending another 60 billion or as much as 75 billion dollars to wage war on Iraq will bury us. We will see oil prices sky rocket and the already low consumer confidence will pale further causing even more grief on Wall Street.<br>
<br>
